TI  - Livelihood of coastal people of Patuakhali and their resilience to natural hazards.
T2  - International Journal of Sustainable Agricultural Technology
M3  - Journal article
AB  - A survey based research work was carried out in the coastal area of Patuakhali district. In two coastal upazillas of Patuakhali, Kalapara and Galachipa, eight wards/villages were investigated during March 2008 to February, 2009. The objective of the present work was to study the life style and livelihood of the coastal inhabitants and their resilience to natural hazards like cyclone and storm surge. Information was also received from the leaflets, booklets, official records of various organizations on personal contact. Some striking findings are mentioned here,: i. Inhabitants are vulnerable to coastal hazards like tidal surge, storm, cyclone due to degeneration of the Sundarbans and serious damage of the coastal embankment ii. The inhabitants are 30% fisherman 20% farmer, 20% petty business and 30% daily labors. In financial consideration about 10% people are solvent, businessman, 90% of the inhabitants are poor, iii. Condition of the dwelling house is miserable, iv. Sanitary latrines and tube wells are mostly supplied free of cost but those are not properly installed and used by the people, v. The poor inhabitants are in the primitive stage of soil life only and vi. The poor coastal inhabitants have no interest for education they always look for food and shelter.
