AB  - The arid region is characterized by fragile ecosystem. Due to frequent droughts arable farming is a gamble. Tree is central to production and function in this region. It is also central to arable farming and animal husbandry. Over fifty years of research at CAZRI have shown that growing tree on agricultural and non agricultural fields conserves soil and rain water, enrich soils and produce biomass which can be used as food, fodder and fuel.
