TI  - Livestock and climate change - impacts and adaptation.
T2  - Agriculture for Development
M3  - Journal article
AB  - In this article the effects of climate change on livestock production with special focus its impact on the systems of smallholders and pastoralists was discussed. Highlights of the discussion is on the direct impact of climate change on livestock brought by drought, flood episodes and its impacts on rangelands, pastures and cultivated forages, and on the health and diseases of animals. A brief dicussion on the indirect impacts of climate change as well as how farmers adapt to this changes were also included.
