TI  - Abstracts of the XVI Meeting of field epidemiologists, Colombia, 2012.
T2  - Informe Quincenal - Epidemiologico Nacional
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This issue contains several abstracts of studies presented during an epidemiological conference in Colombia in 2012. Surveillance data on demography, mortality, prevalence and risk factors during different time periods are presented. Diseases and abnormalities mentioned are as follows: malaria; papular urticaria by flea bite; low birth weight; quality of vital statistics of births, behaviour of pathogens associated with foodborne disease outbreaks; Ciguatera and fish consumption; occupational exposure to pesticides in potato farmers; needs of mental health workers who care emergencies, epidemics and disasters; suicides; congenital malformations; and maternal morbidity and mortality. The importance of data surveillance and good data quality is emphasized.
