AU  - Hiralal Jana, Hiralal Jana
AU  - Debabrata Basu, Debabrata Basu
TI  - Problems faced by fishermen in their fish farming in Moyna block of West Bengal.
T2  - Journal of Interacademicia
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Fisheries are playing a key role in the changing profile of Indian economic growth. India is to sustain 16 per cent of the world's population on 2.4 percent of the global land area. It has to feed its burgeoning population using 3 percent and 5 percent of global farm land and water resources. Hence, its dependence on aquatic resources for production of additional food is obvious and shall become more and more obligatory. Presently, the fish cultivation is under grasp of many problems. Therefore, the present study was conducted to identify the various problems faced by fishermen in their farming. The study was undertaken in Moyna block of East Midnapur district of West Bengal. The study revealed that fishermen of the study area faced the major problems, those were-(1) Price of fish feed is very high (100%) (2) Transportation cost is very high (100%) (3) Scarcity of water at summer season (100%) (4) Lack of good road condition (100%) (5) Adulterated fish feed (100%) (6) Flood problem (100%) (7) No option to lift ground water (100%) (8) Maintain the fish pond bund is a problem (91%) and (9) Market price of fish is less (88%). Therefore, the extension agencies, public or private are working in the study area will consider these problems heartily and will try to find out the possible ways to remove those problems according to their level best.
