TI  - Evaluation of the clinical parameters of girolanda cattle in an agricultural exhibition in Alagoas.
T2  - Medicina Veterinaria (Brasil)
M3  - Journal article
M3  - Conference paper
AB  - The objective of this study was to evaluate the clinical parameters of Girolanda cattle in an agricultural exhibition in the Municipality of Maceio, Alagoas, Brazil. 43 cattle males and females aged between six and 44 months and weighing from 257.7 to 583 kg were evaluated for rectal temperature (RT), respiratory rate (RR), heart rate (FC), capillary refill time (TPC), turgor, lymph nodes, mucosal colour and motility. The animals were divided according to age into G1 (seven to 12 months), G2 (13 to 24 months) and G3 (27 to 44 months) at two moments of analysis, morning (M0) and afternoon. (M1). Changes were observed in the parameters between the moments of analysis; however, all parameters were within normal limits, with the exception of the RF in G3 in M0 and M1. The animals showed changes in clinical parameters, where higher environmental temperatures and an increase in the number of RF were observed, which is the first visible sign of animals subjected to heat stress. In conclusion, the use of good practices for the welfare of cattle from an agricultural exhibition are sufficient to maintain good levels of animal welfare.
