AU  - Duan, Guang-Fu
AU  - Hu, Xiao-Yan
TI  - Impact and countermeasures of river regulation projects on the aquatic ecosystem of the main stream of the Yangtze river - taking the emergency governance project of bank collapse in the Jiangxi section of the Yangtze river as an example.
T2  - Journal of Anhui Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Taking the emergency governance project of bank collapse in the Jiangxi section of the Yangtze River as an example, this paper systematically analyzes the impact of river regulation projects on the aquatic ecosystem of the Yangtze River main stream and proposes targeted countermeasures. The results show that the river regulation project can effectively maintain the stability of the river regime and ensure flood safety through the construction and reinforcement of bank protection. However, the water?related operations during the construction period lead to a significant increase in the concentration of suspended solids in the local water area. The interference of suspended solids and habitat disturbance have short?term adverse effects on the reproduction and habitat of aquatic organisms. It is predicted that the loss of phytoplankton is 1.782 tons, zooplankton is 0.319 tons, benthic organism is 2.159 tons, and fish fry is about 52 500. Through the comprehensive protection system of "avoidance-restoration-compensation-monitoring", and by taking comprehensive measures such as avoiding construction during the breeding period, setting up artificial fish nests, compensating fishery resources and ecological restoration, the impact of the project on the aquatic ecosystem of the Yangtze River main stream can be controlled within an acceptable range.
