TY  - JOUR
AU  - Zhao HongHai, Zhao HongHai
AU  - Gao CuiZhu, Gao CuiZhu
AU  - Liang Chen, Liang Chen
TI  - Effects of soil drought on the occurrence dynamics of Heterodera avenaein wheat field.
T2  - Journal of Plant Protection
M3  - Journal article
AB  - In order to clarify the effects of soil drought on the wheat field occurrence dynamics of Heterodera avanae(Ha), Ha samples were periodically collected from the irrigated and non-irrigated plots, in 2014, and the occurrence densities of each Ha stage in both plots were determined by using the microscopic examination of the nematodes. The results showed that from April to May, the population densities of the 2nd stage juveniles (J2) and white female in soil, J2 and 3rd-4th stage juveniles (J3+J4) in root were all higher in the irrigated plot than those in the non-irrigated plots. Especially in April, the average densities of emerged and penetrated J2 were 3.0/100 g of soil and 19.0/10 g of root in the irrigated plots, but those were only 0.6/100 g of soil and 19.0/10 g of root in the non-irrigated plots. During the wheat growing season, the Ha cyst population density increased slightly, with the reproduction factor (Rf) of 1.04, in the irrigated plot, but the cyst density reduced dramatically, with the Rfof 0.09, in the non-irrigated plot. The results indicated that severe soil drought inhibited the emergence and penetration of Ha J2, reduced the occurring amounts of J3 or J4 and females, and resulted in the Rfsignificant decline.
PU  - Editorial Board of the Journal of Plant Protection
