TI  - 3rd International Conference on Integrated Coastal Management & Marine Biotechnology, Bogor City, Indonesia, 11-12 August 2021.
T2  - IOP Conference Series : Earth and Environmental Science
M3  - Journal issue
M3  - Conference proceedings
AB  - This conference provided a forum for integrated coastal management (ICM) and marine biotechnology (MBT) experts and practitioners to meet and discuss their frontier ICM practices, as well as the latest scientific-based approaches/methodologies/tools and technological advancements in this important field. The conference also aimed to advance the participants' understanding of local, regional and global ICM problems and their solutions. A total of 54 papers from the conference are presented, covering the ICM themes of: marine protected areas, coastal resources and ecosystem rehabilitation, sustainable fisheries management and ecosystem approach to fisheries management, coastal disaster risk reduction and climate change impact and adaptation management, community livelihood enhancement, ecosystem services and valuation, and marine spatial planning. Besides ICM-related themes, this conference also discussed the latest developments in marine biotechnology covering bioprospecting, marine natural products, and marine environmental biotechnology.
