TI  - Special Issue: Action ready climate knowledge to improve disaster risk management of smallholder farmers in the Philippines.
T2  - Philippine Agricultural Scientist
M3  - Journal issue
AB  - The 12 papers in this special issue offer insights into the process of creating value from PAGASA (Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration) information for smallholder farmers. These 12 papers are drawn from case studies in two contrasting farming systems: high-value vegetable production in Benguet, and maize and rice production in Mindoro. The papers have a common focus on the use of weather and climate information for smallholder farmers, but they apply various methods from the social sciences (social network analysis, key informant interviews, gender analysis) and applied economics (risk matrices, simulation model, decision analysis, and value of information).
