AU  - Tomlinson, Jhannel
AU  - Navarrete-Frias, Carolina
TI  - Climate-smart agriculture investment portfolios for the southern plains in Jamaica.
T2  - CIAT Policy Briefs
M3  - Bulletin
AB  - This report discusses the vulnerability of Jamaica's Southern Plains to climate change and the need for climate-smart agriculture (CSA) investment portfolios to enhance resilience. The region faces increasing temperatures, reduced rainfall, and water scarcity, impacting agricultural productivity. Access to water and financial instruments is limited, and farmers require training to adopt new technologies. The report highlights the importance of gender and social inclusion, particularly for women and youth. A framework for prioritizing CSA interventions was developed, integrating various tools and methods to identify context-specific technologies and assess trade-offs. The framework was applied in collaboration with local communities, focusing on value chain characterization and co-creation of training programmes. Policy recommendations include capacity building for extension services, and exploring financing mechanisms to support CSA implementation. Innovative market mechanisms and strategic land-use planning are also suggested to enhance agricultural resilience and food security.
