TI  - Flatfish farming.
T2  - Aquaculture in China: success stories and modern trends
M3  - Book chapter
AB  - This chapter describes biological characteristics of turbot, Japanese flounde, and half-smooth tongue sole. Chinese flatfish aquaculture industry consists of five facets: seed production, nursery, grow-out live fish transportation, and marketing. A large-scale industry belt for flatfish farming developed along the Bohai Sea ring area and along the northern coast of the Yellow Sea facilitated the economic development of agriculture, the countryside and farmers. An environmentally friendly circulating-water pond-farming mode has been developed that is characterized by high efficiency and high output, which increase the popularity of this new pond farming mode. To achieve sustainable development, disease control measures need to be strengthened. Use of vaccines, and training for standard use of drugs according to national policies and regulations need to be implemented. The sustainable development of China's aquaculture industry is affected by factors such as economic instability, high risks inherent in breeding, lack of processing industries, and water scarcity.
