TI  - Analysis on agronomic traits and breeding for a new winter wheat variety 'Longyu No. 4' with high yield and drought resistence.
T2  - Southwest China Journal of Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Longyu No. 4 was bred by College of Agriculture and Forestry of Longdong University in 2000. Taken Xifeng No. 20 as female and Zhong 210 as male in sexual hybridization, the new varieties of dryland winter wheat was bred with the pedigree method. The results showed that the average yield of Longyu No. 4 was 3922.50 and 4013.48 kg/hm2in regional trial of Gansu province and semiarid areas of northern winter wheat zone from 2008 to 2010. There was an obvious significance that the yields increased by 13.39% and 6.04%, compared to the control. The 3 years production ranks was the first, the first rate was 100%, and the rate of production was 86.7%. The average yield was 4722.9 kg/hm2in 2010 production test of Gansu province and 15.21% higher than that of Xifeng No. 27 (CK). The Shukla variation coefficient was 3.9576%-7.3098% in 2-year national regional trials, the variation coefficient was 17.19%-29.34%, the fitness was 77.8%-80%, the drought resistant index was 1.105-1.292, the death rate of overwintering strains was from 10.3% to 12.1%, the death rate of overwintering stems was 12.5%-14.4%, and the property of drought resistance and cold resistance was 2. The experimental demonstration showed that Longyu No. 4 had high yield, good stability and wide adaptability, and it had broad application prospects in northern dryland.
