TI  - Review of tropical reservoirs and their fisheries: the cases of Lake Nasser, Lake Volta and Indo-Gangetic Basin reservoir.
T2  - FAO Fisheries and Aquaculture Technical Paper
M3  - Bulletin
AB  - The knowledge accumulated for reservoirs in 3 very different tropical systems (northern India and Pakistan in the Indus and Ganges systems, Lake Nasser in the Nile River Basin and Lake Volta in the Volta River Basin) are reviewed. Data and information on hydrological, biophysical and limnological features, primary production, fish and fisheries have been compiled from grey and published literature, providing a baseline against to describe and analyse the ecological changes that have taken place since impoundment. Changes in fish catch are discussed in relation to climatic variations, ecological succession and fishing effort. Recommendations for the development of indicators describing the different ecological and economic processes influencing fisheries catches and organization of monitoring systems around these indicators are given.
